    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// ADO items() response wraps results under value[]\n// Normalize each ADO item to: { path, gitObjectType, objectId }\nconst raw = $input.first().json;\nconst items = raw.value || [];\n\n// Skip the folder entry itself (gitObjectType == 'tree')\nreturn items\n  .filter(i => i.gitObjectType === 'blob')\n  .map(i => ({ json: { path: i.path, objectId: i.objectId } }));\n"
      },
      "id": "bdef24a9-71ed-4b7d-8c3e-2ce81a51afec",
      "name": "Normalize ADO list",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "position": [
        720,
        1488
      ],
      "typeVersion": 2
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## ADO CREDENTIAL SETUP\n\nCreate an **HTTP Basic Auth** credential in n8n:\n- **Username**: leave empty (or any string)\n- **Password**: your Azure DevOps Personal Access Token (PAT)\n\nThe PAT needs **Code (Read & Write)** permission on the target repo.\n\nIn your WF-config workflow, replace the GitHub fields with:\n- `ado_organization` - your ADO org name (e.g. mycompany)\n- `ado_project` - the team project name\n- `ado_repo_name` - the Git repository name\n- `repo_workflows_path` - folder path without leading slash (e.g. n8n-workflows)",
        "height": 380,
        "width": 600,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "fce2dbc7-49a5-417c-9b16-80cd4ebb50fb",
